---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="Gabriel Laniewski" description="Software engineer building real-world mobility systems.">
  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-6 py-20 md:py-28">
    <header class="mb-16">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-[2.25rem] font-bold tracking-tight text-[color:var(--color-ink)] leading-tight">
        Gabriel Laniewski
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-4 text-base md:text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        I build real-world mobility systems designed to operate today and evolve toward autonomy.
        Currently the founding engineer at HandyRides — a mobility platform serving under-resourced
        communities, with a long-term goal of driverless transportation. Previously at Epic Systems.
        Based in Chicago.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-base md:text-[1.05rem] leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        I'm particularly drawn to problems where simulation and real-world operation inform each other,
        and to using AI to rapidly explore ideas and tradeoffs that would otherwise take weeks to test by hand.
      </p>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-16">
      <h2 class="mb-5 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
        Projects
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-6">
        <li class="group">
          <a href="/robotaxi" class="block rounded-md border border-[color:var(--color-rule)] p-5 transition hover:border-[color:var(--color-ink)]">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[color:var(--color-ink)] group-hover:underline">
                Robotaxi simulator, Austin
              </h3>
              <span class="shrink-0 text-xs text-[color:var(--color-muted)] font-mono">Apr 2026</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[0.97rem] leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
              Discrete-event sim for a full-city AV ride-hail service over real Austin demand data.
              I wanted to understand the tradeoffs between service quality, fleet size, and charging
              network design — and to document what the sim actually revealed.
            </p>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-[color:var(--color-accent)]">
              Read the post &rarr;
            </p>
          </a>
        </li>

        <li>
          <div class="rounded-md border border-dashed border-[color:var(--color-rule)] p-5">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between gap-6">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
                AI agent for autonomous sim experimentation
              </h3>
              <span class="shrink-0 text-xs text-[color:var(--color-muted)] font-mono">in progress</span>
            </div>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[0.97rem] leading-relaxed text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
              Setting up an AI agent that can run experiments on the robotaxi sim autonomously —
              proposing configurations, interpreting results, and optimizing toward well-defined metrics.
            </p>
          </div>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2 class="mb-4 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.14em] text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">
        Contact
      </h2>
      <ul class="space-y-1.5 text-[0.97rem] text-[color:var(--color-ink-soft)]">
        <li>
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">email</span>
          {" "}&nbsp;
          <a class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)] underline" href="mailto:laniewskigabriel@gmail.com">
            laniewskigabriel@gmail.com
          </a>
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-mono text-sm text-[color:var(--color-muted)]">linkedin</span>
          {" "}&nbsp;
          <a class="text-[color:var(--color-accent)] underline" href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/gabriel-laniewski" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
            linkedin.com/in/gabriel-laniewski
          </a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
